The paper discusses spectral clustering, which is a popular unsupervised learning algorithm in machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses various methods to reduce the computational cost of spectral clustering, which involves numerical linear algebra and graph signal processing techniques, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses the theoretical guarantees of these methods, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories.
